OL,6,FITV will not give up on Channel 3
OL,7,Fanytime in the near future unless Ofcom
OL,8,For government ministers are foolish
OL,9,Fenough to allow this to happen through
OL,10,Feither ineptitude or imposing onerous
OL,11,Fregulations which mean the cost of a
OL,12,FChannel 3 licence exceeds the
OL,13,Fcommercial benefit.
OL,15,FThis is the same ITV which recently
OL,16,Fdoubled the length of its main evening
OL,17,Fnews programme ` presumably in the
OL,18,Fbelief this served its commercial and
OL,19,Fcorporate interests as well as those of
OL,20,Fviewers.
OL,3,CAn internet-only BBC and ITV ditching
OL,4,Cits PSB status: how likely?
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S    G10/12
